Exercises - part 4
1. Prepare a navigation panel that will refer to reports and allow navigation between them.

2. Modify the title of the report using the RDL file for this purpose.

3. Using the available RDL file settings, add a new single-choice parameter named ShowTitle to each of the reports, Yes or No, respectively, Yes by default.

4. Set the option of graph title visibility in one of the reports, depending on the added button.

5. Repeat steps 3 and 4 using the RDL file.

6. Connect to any data set and prepare reports using at least 3 variables.

7. Find the previously added variables in the RDL file and change their names.

8. Change the margins in the RDL file, leaving 1cm on each side. Repeat for two other reports.

